21 struct StackEqn {
22  int4 var1;
23  int4 var2;
24  int4 rhs;
25  static bool compare(const StackEqn &a,const StackEqn &b);
26 };

29 class StackSolver {
30  vector<StackEqn> eqs;
31  vector<StackEqn> guess;
32  vector<Varnode *> vnlist;
33  vector<int4> companion;
34  Address spacebase;
35  vector<int4> soln;
36  int4 missedvariables;
37  void duplicate(void);
38  void propagate(int4 varnum,int4 val);
39 public:
40  void solve(void);
41  void build(const Funcdata &data,AddrSpace *id,int4 spcbase);
42  int4 getNumVariables(void) const { return vnlist.size(); }
43  Varnode *getVariable(int4 i) const { return vnlist[i]; }
44  int4 getCompanion(int4 i) const { return companion[i]; }
45  int4 getSolution(int4 i) const { return soln[i]; }
46 };

63 void StackSolver::propagate(int4 varnum,int4 val)
64 
65 {
66  if (soln[varnum] != 65535) return; // This variable already specified
67  soln[varnum] = val;
68 
69  StackEqn eqn;
70  vector<int4> workstack;
71  workstack.reserve(soln.size());
72  workstack.push_back(varnum);
73  vector<StackEqn>::iterator top;
74 
75  while(!workstack.empty()) {
76  varnum = workstack.back();
77  workstack.pop_back();
78 
79  eqn.var1 = varnum;
80  top = lower_bound(eqs.begin(),eqs.end(),eqn,StackEqn::compare);
81  while((top!=eqs.end())&&((*top).var1 == varnum)) {
82  int4 var2 = (*top).var2;
83  if (soln[var2] == 65535) {
84  soln[var2] = soln[varnum]-(*top).rhs;
85  workstack.push_back(var2);
86  }
87  ++top;
88  }
89  }
90 }

92 void StackSolver::duplicate(void)
93 
94 {
95  int4 size,i;
96  StackEqn eqn;
97 
98  size = eqs.size();
99  for(i=0;i<size;++i) {
100  eqn.var1 = eqs[i].var2;
101  eqn.var2 = eqs[i].var1;
102  eqn.rhs = -eqs[i].rhs;
103  eqs.push_back(eqn);
104  }
105  stable_sort(eqs.begin(),eqs.end(),StackEqn::compare);
106 }

108 void StackSolver::solve(void)
109 
110 {
111  // Use guesses to resolve subsystems not uniquely determined
112  int4 i,size,var1,var2,count,lastcount;
113 
114  soln.clear();
115  soln.resize(vnlist.size(),65535); // Initialize solutions vector
116  duplicate(); // Duplicate and sort the equations
117 
118  propagate(0,0); // We know one variable
119  size = guess.size();
120  lastcount = size+2;
121  do {
122  count = 0;
123  for(i=0;i<size;++i) {
124  var1 = guess[i].var1;
125  var2 = guess[i].var2;
126  if ((soln[var1]!=65535)&&(soln[var2]==65535))
127  propagate(var2,soln[var1]-guess[i].rhs);
128  else if ((soln[var1]==65535)&&(soln[var2]!=65535))
129  propagate(var1,soln[var2]+guess[i].rhs);
130  else if ((soln[var1]==65535)&&(soln[var2]==65535))
131  count += 1;
132  }
133  if (count == lastcount) break;
134  lastcount = count;
135  } while(count > 0);
136 }

143 void StackSolver::build(const Funcdata &data,AddrSpace *id,int4 spcbase)
144 
145 {
146  const VarnodeData &spacebasedata(id->getSpacebase(spcbase));
147  spacebase = Address(spacebasedata.space,spacebasedata.offset);
148  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator begiter,enditer;
149 
150  begiter = data.beginLoc(spacebasedata.size,spacebase);
151  enditer = data.endLoc(spacebasedata.size,spacebase);
152 
153  while(begiter != enditer) { // All instances of the spacebase
154  if ((*begiter)->isFree()) break;
155  vnlist.push_back(*begiter);
156  companion.push_back(-1);
157  ++begiter;
158  }
159  missedvariables = 0;
160  if (vnlist.empty()) return;
161  if (!vnlist[0]->isInput())
162  throw LowlevelError("Input value of stackpointer is not used");
163 
164  vector<Varnode *>::iterator iter;
165  StackEqn eqn;
166  for(int4 i=1;i<vnlist.size();++i) {
167  Varnode *vn = vnlist[i];
168  Varnode *othervn,*constvn;
169  PcodeOp *op = vn->getDef();
170 
171  if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_ADD) {
172  othervn = op->getIn(0);
173  constvn = op->getIn(1);
174  if (othervn->isConstant()) {
175  constvn = othervn;
176  othervn = op->getIn(1);
177  }
178  if (!constvn->isConstant()) { missedvariables+=1; continue; }
179  if (othervn->getAddr() != spacebase) { missedvariables+=1; continue; }
180  iter = lower_bound(vnlist.begin(),vnlist.end(),othervn,Varnode::comparePointers);
181  eqn.var1 = i;
182  eqn.var2 = iter-vnlist.begin();
183  eqn.rhs = constvn->getOffset();
184  eqs.push_back(eqn);
185  }
186  else if (op->code() == CPUI_COPY) {
187  othervn = op->getIn(0);
188  if (othervn->getAddr() != spacebase) { missedvariables+=1; continue; }
189  iter = lower_bound(vnlist.begin(),vnlist.end(),othervn,Varnode::comparePointers);
190  eqn.var1 = i;
191  eqn.var2 = iter-vnlist.begin();
192  eqn.rhs = 0;
193  eqs.push_back(eqn);
194  }
195  else if (op->code() == CPUI_INDIRECT) {
196  othervn = op->getIn(0);
197  if (othervn->getAddr() != spacebase) { missedvariables += 1; continue; }
198  iter = lower_bound(vnlist.begin(),vnlist.end(),othervn,Varnode::comparePointers);
199  eqn.var1 = i;
200  eqn.var2 = iter-vnlist.begin();
201  companion[i] = eqn.var2;
202  Varnode *iopvn = op->getIn(1);
203  if (iopvn->getSpace()->getType()==IPTR_IOP) { // If INDIRECT is due call
204  PcodeOp *iop = PcodeOp::getOpFromConst(iopvn->getAddr());
205  FuncCallSpecs *fc = data.getCallSpecs(iop); // Look up function proto
206  if (fc != (FuncCallSpecs *)0) {
207  if (fc->getExtraPop() != ProtoModel::extrapop_unknown) { // Double check that extrapop is unknown
208  eqn.rhs = fc->getExtraPop(); // As the deindirect process may have filled it in
209  eqs.push_back(eqn);
210  continue;
211  }
212  }
213  }
214 
215  eqn.rhs = 4; // Otherwise make a guess
216  guess.push_back(eqn);
217  }
218  else if (op->code() == CPUI_MULTIEQUAL) {
219  for(int4 j=0;j<op->numInput();++j) {
220  othervn = op->getIn(j);
221  if (othervn->getAddr() != spacebase) { missedvariables += 1; continue; }
222  iter = lower_bound(vnlist.begin(),vnlist.end(),othervn,Varnode::comparePointers);
223  eqn.var1 = i;
224  eqn.var2 = iter-vnlist.begin();
225  eqn.rhs = 0;
226  eqs.push_back(eqn);
227  }
228  }
229  else if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_AND) {
230  // This can occur if a function aligns its stack pointer
231  othervn = op->getIn(0);
232  constvn = op->getIn(1);
233  if (othervn->isConstant()) {
234  constvn = othervn;
235  othervn = op->getIn(1);
236  }
237  if (!constvn->isConstant()) { missedvariables+=1; continue; }
238  if (othervn->getAddr() != spacebase) { missedvariables+=1; continue; }
239  iter = lower_bound(vnlist.begin(),vnlist.end(),othervn,Varnode::comparePointers);
240  eqn.var1 = i;
241  eqn.var2 = iter-vnlist.begin();
242  eqn.rhs = 0; // Treat this as a copy
243  eqs.push_back(eqn);
244  }
245  else
246  missedvariables += 1;
247  }
248 }

257 void ActionStackPtrFlow::analyzeExtraPop(Funcdata &data,AddrSpace *stackspace,int4 spcbase)
258 
259 {
260  ProtoModel *myfp = data.getArch()->evalfp_called;
261  if (myfp == (ProtoModel *)0)
262  myfp = data.getArch()->defaultfp;
263  if (myfp->getExtraPop()!=ProtoModel::extrapop_unknown) return;
264 
265  StackSolver solver;
266  try {
267  solver.build(data,stackspace,spcbase);
268  } catch(LowlevelError &err) {
269  ostringstream s;
270  s << "Stack frame is not setup normally: " << err.explain;
271  data.warningHeader(s.str());
272  return;
273  }
274  if (solver.getNumVariables() == 0) return;
275  solver.solve(); // Solve the equations
276 
277  Varnode *invn = solver.getVariable(0);
278  bool warningprinted = false;
279 
280  for(int4 i=1;i<solver.getNumVariables();++i) {
281  Varnode *vn = solver.getVariable(i);
282  int4 soln = solver.getSolution(i);
283  if (soln == 65535) {
284  if (!warningprinted) {
285  data.warningHeader("Unable to track spacebase fully for "+stackspace->getName());
286  warningprinted = true;
287  }
288  continue;
289  }
290  PcodeOp *op = vn->getDef();
291 
292  if (op->code() == CPUI_INDIRECT) {
293  Varnode *iopvn = op->getIn(1);
294  if (iopvn->getSpace()->getType()==IPTR_IOP) {
295  PcodeOp *iop = PcodeOp::getOpFromConst(iopvn->getAddr());
296  FuncCallSpecs *fc = data.getCallSpecs(iop);
297  if (fc != (FuncCallSpecs *)0) {
298  int4 soln2 = 0;
299  int4 comp = solver.getCompanion(i);
300  if (comp >= 0)
301  soln2 = solver.getSolution(comp);
302  fc->setEffectiveExtraPop(soln-soln2);
303  }
304  }
305  }
306  vector<Varnode *> paramlist;
307  paramlist.push_back(invn);
308  int4 sz = invn->getSize();
309  paramlist.push_back(data.newConstant(sz,soln&calc_mask(sz)));
310  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ADD);
311  data.opSetAllInput(op,paramlist);
312  }
313  return;
314 }

325 bool ActionStackPtrFlow::isStackRelative(Varnode *spcbasein,Varnode *vn,uintb &constval)
326 
327 {
328  if (spcbasein == vn) {
329  constval = 0;
330  return true;
331  }
332  if (!vn->isWritten()) return false;
333  PcodeOp *addop = vn->getDef();
334  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return false;
335  if (addop->getIn(0) != spcbasein) return false;
336  Varnode *constvn = addop->getIn(1);
337  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return false;
338  constval = constvn->getOffset();
339  return true;
340 }

349 bool ActionStackPtrFlow::adjustLoad(Funcdata &data,PcodeOp *loadop,PcodeOp *storeop)
350 
351 {
352  Varnode *vn = storeop->getIn(2);
353  if (vn->isConstant())
354  vn = data.newConstant(vn->getSize(),vn->getOffset());
355  else if (vn->isFree())
356  return false;
357 
358  data.opRemoveInput(loadop,1);
359  data.opSetOpcode(loadop,CPUI_COPY);
360  data.opSetInput(loadop,vn,0);
361  return true;

374 int4 ActionStackPtrFlow::repair(Funcdata &data,AddrSpace *id,Varnode *spcbasein,PcodeOp *loadop,uintb constz)
375 
376 {
377  int4 loadsize = loadop->getOut()->getSize();
378  BlockBasic *curblock = loadop->getParent();
379  list<PcodeOp *>::iterator begiter = curblock->beginOp();
380  list<PcodeOp *>::iterator iter = loadop->getBasicIter();
381  for(;;) {
382  if (iter == begiter) {
383  if (curblock->sizeIn() != 1) return 0; // Can trace back to next basic block if only one path
384  curblock = (BlockBasic *)curblock->getIn(0);
385  begiter = curblock->beginOp();
386  iter = curblock->endOp();
387  continue;
388  }
389  else {
390  --iter;
391  }
392  PcodeOp *curop = *iter;
393  if (curop->isCall()) return 0; // Don't try to trace aliasing through a call
394  if (curop->code() == CPUI_STORE) {
395  Varnode *ptrvn = curop->getIn(1);
396  Varnode *datavn = curop->getIn(2);
397  uintb constnew;
398  if (isStackRelative(spcbasein,ptrvn,constnew)) {
399  if ((constnew == constz)&&(loadsize == datavn->getSize())) {
400  // We found the matching store
401  if (adjustLoad(data,loadop,curop))
402  return 1;
403  return 0;
404  }
405  else if ((constnew <= constz + (loadsize-1))&&(constnew+(datavn->getSize()-1)>=constz))
406  return 0;
407  }
408  else
409  return 0; // Any other kind of STORE we can't solve aliasing
410  }
411  else {
412  Varnode *outvn = curop->getOut();
413  if (outvn != (Varnode *)0) {
414  if (outvn->getSpace() == id) return 0; // Stack already traced, too late
415  }
416  }
417  }
418 }

428 int4 ActionStackPtrFlow::checkClog(Funcdata &data,AddrSpace *id,int4 spcbase)
429 
430 {
431  const VarnodeData &spacebasedata(id->getSpacebase(spcbase));
432  Address spacebase = Address(spacebasedata.space,spacebasedata.offset);
433  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator begiter,enditer;
434  int4 clogcount = 0;
435 
436  begiter = data.beginLoc(spacebasedata.size,spacebase);
437  enditer = data.endLoc(spacebasedata.size,spacebase);
438 
439  Varnode *spcbasein;
440  if (begiter == enditer) return clogcount;
441  spcbasein = *begiter;
442  ++begiter;
443  if (!spcbasein->isInput()) return clogcount;
444  while(begiter != enditer) {
445  Varnode *outvn = *begiter;
446  ++begiter;
447  if (!outvn->isWritten()) continue;
448  PcodeOp *addop = outvn->getDef();
449  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) continue;
450  Varnode *y = addop->getIn(1);
451  if (!y->isWritten()) continue; // y must not be a constant
452  Varnode *x = addop->getIn(0); // is y is not constant than x (in position 0) isn't either
453  uintb constx;
454  if (!isStackRelative(spcbasein,x,constx)) { // If x is not stack relative
455  x = y; // Swap x and y
456  y = addop->getIn(0);
457  if (!isStackRelative(spcbasein,x,constx)) continue; // Now maybe the new x is stack relative
458  }
459  PcodeOp *loadop = y->getDef();
460  if (loadop->code() == CPUI_INT_MULT) { // If we multiply
461  Varnode *constvn = loadop->getIn(1);
462  if (!constvn->isConstant()) continue;
463  if (constvn->getOffset() != calc_mask(constvn->getSize())) continue; // Must multiply by -1
464  y = loadop->getIn(0);
465  if (!y->isWritten()) continue;
466  loadop = y->getDef();
467  }
468  if (loadop->code() != CPUI_LOAD) continue;
469  Varnode *ptrvn = loadop->getIn(1);
470  uintb constz;
471  if (!isStackRelative(spcbasein,ptrvn,constz)) continue;
472  clogcount += repair(data,id,spcbasein,loadop,constz);
473  }
474  return clogcount;
475 }

477 int4 ActionStackPtrFlow::apply(Funcdata &data)
478 
479 {
480  if (analysis_finished)
481  return 0;
482  if (stackspace == (AddrSpace *)0) {
483  analysis_finished = true; // No stack to do analysis on
484  return 0;
485  }
486  int4 numchange = checkClog(data,stackspace,0);
487  if (numchange > 0) {
488  count += 1;
489  }
490  if (numchange == 0) {
491  analyzeExtraPop(data,stackspace,0);
492  analysis_finished = true;
493  }
494  return 0;
495 }

497 int4 ActionSegmentize::apply(Funcdata &data)
498 
499 {
500  int4 numops = data.getArch()->userops.numSegmentOps();
501  if (numops==0) return 0;
502  if (localcount>0) return 0; // Only perform once
503  localcount = 1; // Mark as having performed once
504 
505  vector<Varnode *> bindlist;
506  bindlist.push_back((Varnode *)0);
507  bindlist.push_back((Varnode *)0);
508 
509  for(int4 i=0;i<numops;++i) {
510  SegmentOp *segdef = data.getArch()->userops.getSegmentOp(i);
511  if (segdef == (SegmentOp *)0) continue;
512  AddrSpace *spc = segdef->getSpace();
513 
514  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter,enditer;
515  iter = data.beginOp(CPUI_CALLOTHER);
516  enditer = data.endOp(CPUI_CALLOTHER);
517  int4 uindex = segdef->getIndex();
518  while(iter != enditer) {
519  PcodeOp *segroot = *iter++;
520  if (segroot->isDead()) continue;
521  if (segroot->getIn(0)->getOffset() != uindex) continue;
522  if (!segdef->unify(data,segroot,bindlist)) {
523  ostringstream err;
524  err << "Segment op in wrong form at ";
525  segroot->getAddr().printRaw(err);
526  throw LowlevelError(err.str());
527  }
528 
529  if (segdef->getNumVariableTerms()==1)
530  bindlist[1] = data.newConstant(4,0);
531  // Redefine the op as a segmentop
532  data.opSetOpcode(segroot,CPUI_SEGMENTOP);
533  data.opSetInput(segroot,data.newVarnodeSpace(spc),0);
534  data.opSetInput(segroot,bindlist[1],1);
535  data.opSetInput(segroot,bindlist[0],2);
536  for(int4 j=segroot->numInput()-1;j>2;--j) // Remove anything else
537  data.opRemoveInput(segroot,j);
538  count += 1;
539  }
540  }
541  return 0;
542 }

551 int4 ActionConstbase::apply(Funcdata &data)
552 
553 {
554  if (data.getBasicBlocks().getSize()==0) return 0; // No blocks
555  // Get start block, which is constructed to have nothing
556  // falling into it
557  BlockBasic *bb = (BlockBasic *)data.getBasicBlocks().getBlock(0);
558 
559  int4 injectid = data.getFuncProto().getInjectUponEntry();
560  if (injectid >= 0) {
561  InjectPayload *payload = data.getArch()->pcodeinjectlib->getPayload(injectid);
562  data.doLiveInject(payload,bb->getStart(),bb,bb->beginOp());
563  }
564 
565  const TrackedSet trackset( data.getArch()->context->getTrackedSet(data.getAddress()));
566 
567  for(int4 i=0;i<trackset.size();++i) {
568  const TrackedContext &ctx(trackset[i]);
569 
570  Address addr(ctx.loc.space,ctx.loc.offset);
571  PcodeOp *op = data.newOp(1,bb->getStart());
572  data.newVarnodeOut(ctx.loc.size,addr,op);
573  Varnode *vnin = data.newConstant(ctx.loc.size,ctx.val);
574  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
575  data.opSetInput(op,vnin,0);
576  data.opInsertBegin(op,bb);
577  }
578  return 0;
579 }

614 bool ActionMultiCse::preferredOutput(Varnode *out1,Varnode *out2)
615 
616 {
617  // Prefer the output that is used in a CPUI_RETURN
618  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter,enditer;
619  enditer = out1->endDescend();
620  for(iter=out1->beginDescend();iter!=enditer;++iter) {
621  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
622  if (op->code() == CPUI_RETURN)
623  return false;
624  }
625  enditer = out2->endDescend();
626  for(iter=out2->beginDescend();iter!=enditer;++iter) {
627  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
628  if (op->code() == CPUI_RETURN)
629  return true;
630  }
631  // Prefer addrtied over register over unique
632  if (!out1->isAddrTied()) {
633  if (out2->isAddrTied())
634  return true;
635  else {
636  if (out1->getSpace()->getType()==IPTR_INTERNAL) {
637  if (out2->getSpace()->getType()!=IPTR_INTERNAL)
638  return true;
639  }
640  }
641  }
642  return false;
643 }

650 PcodeOp *ActionMultiCse::findMatch(BlockBasic *bl,PcodeOp *target,Varnode *in)
651 
652 {
653  list<PcodeOp *>::iterator iter = bl->beginOp();
654 
655  for(;;) {
656  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
657  ++iter;
658  if (op == target) // Caught up with target, nothing else before it
659  break;
660  int4 i,numinput;
661  numinput = op->numInput();
662  for(i=0;i<numinput;++i) {
663  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(i);
664  if (vn->isWritten() && (vn->getDef()->code() == CPUI_COPY))
665  vn = vn->getDef()->getIn(0); // Allow for differences in copy propagation
666  if (vn == in) break;
667  }
668  if (i < numinput) {
669  int4 j;
670  Varnode *buf1[2];
671  Varnode *buf2[2];
672  for(j=0;j<numinput;++j) {
673  Varnode *in1 = op->getIn(j);
674  if (in1->isWritten() && (in1->getDef()->code() == CPUI_COPY))
675  in1 = in1->getDef()->getIn(0); // Allow for differences in copy propagation
676  Varnode *in2 = target->getIn(j);
677  if (in2->isWritten() && (in2->getDef()->code() == CPUI_COPY))
678  in2 = in2->getDef()->getIn(0);
679  if (in1 == in2) continue;
680  if (0!=functionalEqualityLevel(in1,in2,buf1,buf2))
681  break;
682  }
683  if (j==numinput) // We have found a redundancy
684  return op;
685  }
686  }
687  return (PcodeOp *)0;
688 }

695 bool ActionMultiCse::processBlock(Funcdata &data,BlockBasic *bl)
696 
697 {
698  vector<Varnode *> vnlist;
699  PcodeOp *targetop = (PcodeOp *)0;
700  PcodeOp *pairop;
701  list<PcodeOp *>::iterator iter = bl->beginOp();
702  list<PcodeOp *>::iterator enditer = bl->endOp();
703  while(iter != enditer) {
704  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
705  ++iter;
706  OpCode opc = op->code();
707  if (opc == CPUI_COPY) continue;
708  if (opc != CPUI_MULTIEQUAL) break;
709  int4 vnpos = vnlist.size();
710  int4 i;
711  int4 numinput = op->numInput();
712  for(i=0;i<numinput;++i) {
713  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(i);
714  if (vn->isWritten() && (vn->getDef()->code() == CPUI_COPY)) // Some copies may not propagate into MULTIEQUAL
715  vn = vn->getDef()->getIn(0); // Allow for differences in copy propagation
716  vnlist.push_back(vn);
717  if (vn->isMark()) { // If we've seen this varnode before
718  pairop = findMatch(bl,op,vn);
719  if (pairop != (PcodeOp *)0)
720  break;
721  }
722  }
723  if (i<numinput) {
724  targetop = op;
725  break;
726  }
727  for(i=vnpos;i<vnlist.size();++i)
728  vnlist[i]->setMark(); // Mark that we have seen this varnode
729  }
730 
731  // Clear out any of the marks we put down
732  for(int4 i=0;i<vnlist.size();++i)
733  vnlist[i]->clearMark();
734 
735  if (targetop != (PcodeOp *)0) {
736  Varnode *out1 = pairop->getOut();
737  Varnode *out2 = targetop->getOut();
738  if (preferredOutput(out1,out2)) {
739  data.totalReplace(out1,out2); // Replace pairop and out1 in favor of targetop and out2
740  data.opDestroy(pairop);
741  }
742  else {
743  data.totalReplace(out2,out1);
744  data.opDestroy(targetop);
745  }
746  count += 1; // Indicate that a change has taken place
747  return true;
748  }
749  return false;
750 }

758  BlockBasic *bl = (BlockBasic *)bblocks.getBlock(i);
759  while(processBlock(data,bl)) {

765 int4 ActionShadowVar::apply(Funcdata &data)
766 
767 {
768  const BlockGraph &bblocks(data.getBasicBlocks());
769  BlockBasic *bl;
770  PcodeOp *op;
771  Varnode *vn;
772  vector<Varnode *> vnlist;
773  list<PcodeOp *> oplist;
774  uintb startoffset;
775  for(int4 i=0;i<bblocks.getSize();++i) {
776  vnlist.clear();
777  bl = (BlockBasic *)bblocks.getBlock(i);
778  // Iterator over all MULTIEQUALs in the block
779  // We have to check all ops in the first address
780  // We cannot stop at first non-MULTIEQUAL because
781  // other ops creep in because of multi_collapse
782  startoffset = bl->getStart().getOffset();
783  list<PcodeOp *>::iterator iter = bl->beginOp();
784  while(iter != bl->endOp()) {
785  op = *iter++;
786  if (op->getAddr().getOffset() != startoffset) break;
787  if (op->code() != CPUI_MULTIEQUAL) continue;
788  vn = op->getIn(0);
789  if (vn->isMark())
790  oplist.push_back(op);
791  else {
792  vn->setMark();
793  vnlist.push_back(vn);
794  }
795  }
796  for(int4 j=0;j<vnlist.size();++j)
797  vnlist[j]->clearMark();
798  }
799  list<PcodeOp *>::iterator oiter;
800  for(oiter=oplist.begin();oiter!=oplist.end();++oiter) {
801  op = *oiter;
802  PcodeOp *op2;
803  for(op2=op->previousOp();op2!=(PcodeOp *)0;op2=op2->previousOp()) {
804  if (op2->code() != CPUI_MULTIEQUAL) continue;
805  int4 i;
806  for(i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) // Check for match in each branch
807  if (op->getIn(i) != op2->getIn(i)) break;
808  if (i != op->numInput()) continue; // All branches did not match
809 
810  vector<Varnode *> plist;
811  plist.push_back(op2->getOut());
812  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
813  data.opSetAllInput(op,plist);
814  count += 1;
815  }
816  }
817 
818  return 0;
819 }

830 SymbolEntry *ActionConstantPtr::isPointer(AddrSpace *spc,Varnode *vn,PcodeOp *op,Address &rampoint,Funcdata &data)
831 
832 {
833  bool needexacthit;
834  Architecture *glb = data.getArch();
835  Varnode *outvn;
836  if (vn->getType()->getMetatype() == TYPE_PTR) { // Are we explicitly marked as a pointer
837  rampoint = glb->resolveConstant(spc,vn->getOffset(),vn->getSize(),op->getAddr());
838  needexacthit = false;
839  }
840  else {
841  if (vn->isTypeLock()) return (SymbolEntry *)0; // Locked as NOT a pointer
842  needexacthit = true;
843  // Check if the constant is involved in a potential pointer expression
844  // as the base
845  switch(op->code()) {
846  case CPUI_RETURN:
847  case CPUI_CALL:
848  case CPUI_CALLIND:
849  // A constant parameter or return value could be a pointer
850  if (!glb->infer_pointers)
851  return (SymbolEntry *)0;
852  if (op->getSlot(vn)==0)
853  return (SymbolEntry *)0;
854  break;
855  case CPUI_COPY:
856  case CPUI_INT_EQUAL:
857  case CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL:
858  case CPUI_INT_LESS:
859  case CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL:
860  // A comparison with a constant could be a pointer
861  break;
862  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
863  outvn = op->getOut();
864  if (outvn->getType()->getMetatype()==TYPE_PTR) {
865  int4 slot = op->getSlot(vn);
866  // Is there another pointer base in this expression
867  if (op->getIn(1-slot)->getType()->getMetatype()==TYPE_PTR)
868  return (SymbolEntry *)0; // If so, we are not a pointer
869  // FIXME: need to fully explore additive tree
870  needexacthit = false;
871  }
872  else if (!glb->infer_pointers)
873  return (SymbolEntry *)0;
874  break;
875  default:
876  return (SymbolEntry *)0;
877  }
878  // Make sure the constant is in the expected range for a pointer
879  if ((glb->pointer_lowerbound != 0)&&(glb->pointer_lowerbound > vn->getOffset()))
880  return (SymbolEntry *)0;
881  // Check if the constant looks like a single bit or mask
882  if (bit_transitions(vn->getOffset(),vn->getSize()) < 3)
883  return (SymbolEntry *)0;
884  rampoint = glb->resolveConstant(spc,vn->getOffset(),vn->getSize(),op->getAddr());
885  }
886 
887  if (rampoint.isInvalid()) return (SymbolEntry *)0;
888  // Since we are looking for a global address
889  // Assume it is address tied and use empty usepoint
890  SymbolEntry *entry = data.getScopeLocal()->getParent()->queryContainer(rampoint,1,Address());
891  if (needexacthit&&(entry != (SymbolEntry *)0)) {
892  if (entry->getAddr() != rampoint)
893  return (SymbolEntry *)0;
894  }
895  return entry;
896 }

898 int4 ActionConstantPtr::apply(Funcdata &data)
899 
900 {
901  if (!data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) return 0;
902 
903  if (localcount >= 4) // At most 4 passes (once type recovery starts)
904  return 0;
905  localcount += 1;
906 
907  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator begiter,enditer;
908  Architecture *glb = data.getArch();
909  AddrSpace *cspc = glb->getConstantSpace();
910  AddrSpace *rspc = glb->getDefaultSpace();
911  SymbolEntry *entry;
912  Varnode *vn;
913  bool arenearpointers = glb->hasNearPointers(rspc);
914  int4 minsize = rspc->isTruncated() ? rspc->getAddrSize() : 0;
915  if (minsize > 0)
916  arenearpointers = true;
917 
918  begiter = data.beginLoc(cspc);
919  enditer = data.endLoc(cspc);
920 
921  while(begiter!=enditer) {
922  vn = *begiter++;
923  if (!vn->isConstant()) break; // New varnodes may get inserted between begiter and enditer
924  if (vn->getOffset() == 0) continue; // Never make constant 0 into spacebase
925  if (vn->isPtrCheck()) continue; // Have we checked this variable before
926  if (vn->hasNoDescend()) continue;
927  if (vn->isSpacebase()) continue; // Don't use constant 0 which is already spacebase
928  // if (vn->getSize() != rspc->getAddrSize()) continue; // Must be size of pointer
929 
930  PcodeOp *op = vn->loneDescend();
931  if (op == (PcodeOp *)0) continue;
932  if (arenearpointers) {
933  if (vn->getSize() < minsize) continue;
934  }
935  else {
936  if (vn->getSize() != rspc->getAddrSize()) continue;
937  }
938  int4 slot = op->getSlot(vn);
939  OpCode opc = op->code();
940  if (opc == CPUI_INT_ADD) {
941  if (op->getIn(1-slot)->isSpacebase()) continue; // Make sure other side is not a spacebase already
942  }
943  else if ((opc == CPUI_PTRSUB)||(opc==CPUI_PTRADD))
944  continue;
945  Address rampoint;
946  entry = isPointer(rspc,vn,op,rampoint,data);
947  vn->setPtrCheck(); // Set check flag AFTER searching for symbol
948  if (entry != (SymbolEntry *)0) {
949  data.spacebaseConstant(op,slot,entry,rampoint,vn->getOffset(),vn->getSize());
950  if ((opc == CPUI_INT_ADD)&&(slot==1))
951  data.opSwapInput(op,0,1);
952  count += 1;
953  }
954  }
955  return 0;
956 }

958 int4 ActionDeindirect::apply(Funcdata &data)
959 
960 {
961  FuncCallSpecs *fc;
962  PcodeOp *op;
963  Varnode *vn;
964 
965  for(int4 i=0;i<data.numCalls();++i) {
966  fc = data.getCallSpecs(i);
967  op = fc->getOp();
968  if (op->code() != CPUI_CALLIND) continue;
969  vn = op->getIn(0);
970  while(vn->isWritten()&&(vn->getDef()->code()==CPUI_COPY))
971  vn = vn->getDef()->getIn(0);
972  if (vn->isPersist() && vn->isExternalRef()) { // Check for possible external reference
973  Funcdata *newfd = data.getScopeLocal()->getParent()->queryExternalRefFunction(vn->getAddr());
974  if (newfd != (Funcdata *)0) {
975  fc->deindirect(data,newfd);
976  count += 1;
977  continue;
978  }
979  }
980  else if (vn->isConstant()) {
981  AddrSpace *sp = data.getAddress().getSpace(); // Assume function is in same space as calling function
982  // Convert constant to a byte address in this space
983  uintb offset = AddrSpace::addressToByte(vn->getOffset(),sp->getWordSize());
984  int4 align = data.getArch()->funcptr_align;
985  if (align != 0) { // If we know function pointer should be aligned
986  offset >>= align; // Remove any encoding bits before querying for the function
987  offset <<= align;
988  }
989  Address codeaddr(sp,offset);
990  Funcdata *newfd = data.getScopeLocal()->getParent()->queryFunction(codeaddr);
991  if (newfd != (Funcdata *)0) {
992  fc->deindirect(data,newfd);
993  count += 1;
994  continue;
995  }
996  }
997  if (data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) {
998  // Check for a function pointer that has an attached prototype
999  Datatype *ct = op->getIn(0)->getType();
1000  if ((ct->getMetatype()==TYPE_PTR)&&
1001  (((TypePointer *)ct)->getPtrTo()->getMetatype()==TYPE_CODE)) {
1002  TypeCode *tc = (TypeCode *)((TypePointer *)ct)->getPtrTo();
1003  const FuncProto *fp = tc->getPrototype();
1004  if (fp!=(const FuncProto *)0) {
1005  if (!fc->isInputLocked()) {
1006  // We use isInputLocked as a test of whether the
1007  // function pointer prototype has been applied before
1008  fc->forceSet(data,*fp);
1009  data.updateOpFromSpec(fc);
1010  count += 1;
1011  }
1012  }
1013  // FIXME: If fc's input IS locked presumably this means
1014  // that this prototype is already set, but it MIGHT mean
1015  // we have conflicting locked prototypes
1016  }
1017  }
1018  }
1019  return 0;

1023 
1024 {

1026  bool cachereadonly = glb->readonlypropagate;

1028  if (!cachereadonly)

1070 int4 ActionDirectWrite::apply(Funcdata &data)
1071 
1072 {
1073  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator iter;
1074  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator oiter;
1075  Varnode *vn,*dvn;
1076  PcodeOp *op;
1077  vector<Varnode *> worklist;
1078 
1079  // Collect legal inputs and other auto direct writes
1080  for(iter=data.beginLoc();iter!=data.endLoc();++iter) {
1081  vn = *iter;
1082  vn->clearDirectWrite();
1083  if (vn->isInput()) {
1084  if (vn->isPersist()||vn->isSpacebase()) {
1085  vn->setDirectWrite();
1086  worklist.push_back(vn);
1087  }
1088  else if (data.getFuncProto().possibleInputParam(vn->getAddr(),vn->getSize())) {
1089  vn->setDirectWrite();
1090  worklist.push_back(vn);
1091  }
1092  }
1093  else if (vn->isWritten()) {
1094  op = vn->getDef();
1095  if (!op->isMarker()) {
1096  if (vn->isPersist()) {
1097  // Anything that writes to a global variable (in a real way) is considered a direct write
1098  vn->setDirectWrite();
1099  worklist.push_back(vn);
1100  }
1101  else if (op->code() == CPUI_COPY) { // For most COPYs, do not consider it a direct write
1102  if (vn->isStackStore()) { // But, if the original operation was really a CPUI_STORE
1103  Varnode *invn = op->getIn(0); // Trace COPY source
1104  if (invn->isWritten()) { // Through possible multiple COPYs
1105  PcodeOp *curop = invn->getDef();
1106  if (curop->code() == CPUI_COPY)
1107  invn = curop->getIn(0);
1108  }
1109  if (invn->isWritten() && invn->getDef()->isMarker()) { // if source is from an INDIRECT
1110  vn->setDirectWrite(); // then treat this as a direct write
1111  worklist.push_back(vn);
1112  }
1113  }
1114  }
1115  else if ((op->code()!=CPUI_PIECE)&&(op->code()!=CPUI_SUBPIECE)) {
1116  // Anything that writes to a variable in a way that isn't some form of COPY is a direct write
1117  vn->setDirectWrite();
1118  worklist.push_back(vn);
1119  }
1120  }
1121  else if (!propagateIndirect && op->code() == CPUI_INDIRECT) {
1122  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
1123  if (op->getIn(0)->getAddr() != outvn->getAddr()) // Check if storage address changes from input to output
1124  vn->setDirectWrite(); // Indicates an active COPY, which is a direct write
1125  else if (outvn->isPersist()) // Value must be present at global storage at point call is made
1126  vn->setDirectWrite(); // so treat as direct write
1127  // We do NOT add vn to worklist as INDIRECT otherwise does not propagate
1128  }
1129  }
1130  else if (vn->isConstant()) {
1131  if (!vn->isIndirectZero()) {
1132  vn->setDirectWrite();
1133  worklist.push_back(vn);
1134  }
1135  }
1136  }
1137  // Let legalness taint
1138  while(!worklist.empty()) {
1139  vn = worklist.back();
1140  worklist.pop_back();
1141  for(oiter=vn->beginDescend();oiter!=vn->endDescend();++oiter) {
1142  op = *oiter;
1143  if (!op->isAssignment()) continue;
1144  dvn = op->getOut();
1145  if (!dvn->isDirectWrite()) {
1146  dvn->setDirectWrite();
1147  if (propagateIndirect || op->code() != CPUI_INDIRECT) // If INDIRECT, output is marked, but does not propagate
1148  worklist.push_back(dvn);
1149  }
1150  }
1151  }
1152  return 0;
1153 }

1193 void ActionFuncLink::funcLinkInput(FuncCallSpecs *fc,Funcdata &data)
1194 
1195 {

1197  bool varargs = fc->isDotdotdot();

1200

1219  loadval->setSpacebasePlaceholder();
1220  spacebase = (AddrSpace *)0; // With a locked stack parameter, we don't need a stackplaceholder
1221  }
1222  }
1223  else

1225  }
1226  }
1227  if (spacebase != (AddrSpace *)0) { // If we need it, create the stackplaceholder
1228  PcodeOp *op = fc->getOp();
1229  int4 slot = op->numInput();
1230  Varnode *loadval = data.opStackLoad(spacebase,0,1,op,(Varnode *)0,false);
1231  data.opInsertInput(op,loadval,slot);

1277 int4 ActionFuncLink::apply(Funcdata &data)

1538 void ActionReturnRecovery::buildReturnOutput(ParamActive *active,PcodeOp *retop,Funcdata &data)
1539 
1540 {
1541  vector<Varnode *> newparam;
1542 
1543  newparam.push_back(retop->getIn(0)); // Keep the first param (the return indirect reference)
1544  for(int4 i=0;i<active->getNumTrials();++i) { // Gather all the used varnodes to this return in proper order
1545  ParamTrial &curtrial(active->getTrial(i));
1546  if (!curtrial.isUsed()) break;
1547  if (curtrial.getSlot() >= retop->numInput()) break;
1548  newparam.push_back(retop->getIn(curtrial.getSlot()));
1549  }
1550  if (newparam.size()<=2) // Easy zero or one return varnode case
1551  data.opSetAllInput(retop,newparam);
1552  else if (newparam.size()==3) { // Two piece concatenation case
1553  Varnode *lovn = newparam[1];
1554  Varnode *hivn = newparam[2];
1555  ParamTrial &triallo( active->getTrial(0) );
1556  ParamTrial &trialhi( active->getTrial(1) );
1557  Address joinaddr = data.getArch()->constructJoinAddress(data.getArch()->translate,
1558  trialhi.getAddress(),trialhi.getSize(),
1559  triallo.getAddress(),triallo.getSize());

1561  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_PIECE);
1562  Varnode *newwhole = data.newVarnodeOut(trialhi.getSize()+triallo.getSize(),joinaddr,newop);
1563  data.opInsertBefore(newop,retop);
1564  newparam.pop_back();
1565  newparam.back() = newwhole;
1566  data.opSetAllInput(retop,newparam);
1567  data.opSetInput(newop,hivn,0);
1568  data.opSetInput(newop,lovn,1);
1569  }
1570  else { // We may have several varnodes from a single container
1571  // Concatenate them into a single result
1572  newparam.clear();
1573  newparam.push_back(retop->getIn(0));
1574  int4 offmatch = 0;
1575  Varnode *preexist = (Varnode *)0;
1576  for(int4 i=0;i<active->getNumTrials();++i) {
1577  ParamTrial &curtrial(active->getTrial(i));
1578  if (!curtrial.isUsed()) break;
1579  if (curtrial.getSlot() >= retop->numInput()) break;
1580  if (preexist == (Varnode *)0) {
1581  preexist = retop->getIn(curtrial.getSlot());
1582  offmatch = curtrial.getOffset() + curtrial.getSize();
1583  }
1584  else if (offmatch == curtrial.getOffset()) {
1585  offmatch += curtrial.getSize();
1586  Varnode *vn = retop->getIn(curtrial.getSlot());
1587  // Concatenate the preexisting pieces with this new piece
1588  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,retop->getAddr());
1589  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_PIECE);
1590  Address addr = preexist->getAddr();
1591  if (vn->getAddr() < addr)
1592  addr = vn->getAddr();
1593  Varnode *newout = data.newVarnodeOut(preexist->getSize()+vn->getSize(),addr,newop);
1594  data.opSetInput(newop,vn,0); // Most sig part
1595  data.opSetInput(newop,preexist,1);
1596  data.opInsertBefore(newop,retop);
1597  preexist = newout;
1598  }
1599  else
1600  break;
1601  }
1602  if (preexist != (Varnode *)0)
1603  newparam.push_back(preexist);
1604  data.opSetAllInput(retop,newparam);
1605  }

1741 bool ActionLikelyTrash::traceTrash(Varnode *vn,vector<PcodeOp *> &indlist)
1742 
1743 {
1744  vector<PcodeOp *> allroutes; // Keep track of merging ops (with more than 1 input)
1745  vector<Varnode *> markedlist; // All varnodes we have visited on paths from -vn-
1746  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter,enditer;
1747  Varnode *outvn;
1748  uintb val;
1749  uint4 traced = 0;
1750  vn->setMark();
1751  markedlist.push_back(vn);
1752  bool istrash = true;
1753 
1754  while(traced < markedlist.size()) {
1755  Varnode *curvn = markedlist[traced++];
1756  iter = curvn->beginDescend();
1757  enditer = curvn->endDescend();
1758  for(;iter!=enditer;++iter) {
1759  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
1760  outvn = op->getOut();
1761  switch(op->code()) {
1762  case CPUI_INDIRECT:
1763  if (outvn->isPersist())
1764  istrash = false;
1765  else
1766  indlist.push_back(op);
1767  break;
1768  case CPUI_SUBPIECE:
1769  if (outvn->isPersist())
1770  istrash = false;
1771  else {
1772  if (!outvn->isMark()) {
1773  outvn->setMark();
1774  markedlist.push_back(outvn);
1775  }
1776  }
1777  break;
1778  case CPUI_MULTIEQUAL:
1779  case CPUI_PIECE:
1780  if (outvn->isPersist())
1781  istrash = false;
1782  else {
1783  if (!op->isMark()) {
1784  op->setMark();
1785  allroutes.push_back(op);
1786  }
1787  uint4 nummark = countMarks(op);
1788  if (nummark == op->numInput()) {
1789  if (!outvn->isMark()) {
1790  outvn->setMark();
1791  markedlist.push_back(outvn);
1792  }
1793  }
1794  }
1795  break;
1796  case CPUI_INT_AND:
1797  // If the AND is using only the topmost significant bytes then it is likely trash
1798  if (op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) {
1799  val = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1800  uintb mask = calc_mask(op->getIn(1)->getSize());
1801  if ((val == ((mask<<8)&mask))||(val == ((mask<<16)&mask))||(val==((mask<<32)&mask))) {
1802  indlist.push_back(op);
1803  break;
1804  }
1805  }
1806  istrash = false;
1807  break;
1808  default:
1809  istrash = false;
1810  break;
1811  }
1812  if (!istrash) break;
1813  }
1814  if (!istrash) break;
1815  }
1816 
1817  for(uint4 i=0;i<allroutes.size();++i) {
1818  if (!allroutes[i]->getOut()->isMark())
1819  istrash = false; // Didn't see all inputs
1820  allroutes[i]->clearMark();
1821  }
1822  for(uint4 i=0;i<markedlist.size();++i)
1823  markedlist[i]->clearMark();
1824 
1825  return istrash;
1826 }

1832 
1833  int4 num = data.getFuncProto().numLikelyTrash();
1834  for(int4 j=0;j<num;++j) {
1835  const VarnodeData &vdata( data.getFuncProto().getLikelyTrash(j) );
1836  Varnode *vn = data.findCoveredInput(vdata.size,vdata.getAddr());

1936 int4 ActionSetCasts::castOutput(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data,CastStrategy *castStrategy)
1937 
1938 {
1939  Datatype *outct,*ct,*tokenct;
1940  Varnode *vn,*outvn;
1941  PcodeOp *newop;
1942  bool force=false;
1943 
1944  tokenct = op->getOpcode()->getOutputToken(op,castStrategy);
1945  outvn = op->getOut();
1946  if (outvn->isImplied()) {
1947  // implied varnode must have parse type
1948  if (outvn->getType()->getMetatype() != TYPE_PTR) // If implied varnode has an atomic (non-pointer) type
1949  outvn->updateType(tokenct,false,false); // Ignore it in favor of the token type
1950  else if (tokenct->getMetatype() == TYPE_PTR) { // If the token is a pointer AND implied varnode is pointer
1951  outct = ((TypePointer *)outvn->getType())->getPtrTo();
1952  type_metatype meta = outct->getMetatype();
1953  // Preserve implied pointer if it points to a composite
1954  if ((meta!=TYPE_ARRAY)&&(meta!=TYPE_STRUCT))
1955  outvn->updateType(tokenct,false,false); // Otherwise ignore it in favor of the token type
1956  }
1957  if (outvn->getType() != tokenct)
1958  force=true; // Make sure not to drop pointer type
1959  }
1960  if (!force) {
1961  outct = outvn->getHigh()->getType(); // Type of result
1962  ct = castStrategy->castStandard(outct,tokenct,false,true);
1963  if (ct == (Datatype *)0) return 0;
1964  }
1965  // Generate the cast op
1966  vn = data.newUnique(op->getOut()->getSize());
1967  vn->updateType(tokenct,false,false);
1968  vn->setImplied();
1969  newop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
1970 #ifdef CPUI_STATISTICS
1971  data.getArch()->stats->countCast();
1972 #endif
1973  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_CAST);
1974  data.opSetOutput(newop,op->getOut());
1975  data.opSetInput(newop,vn,0);
1976  data.opSetOutput(op,vn);
1977  data.opInsertAfter(newop,op); // Cast comes AFTER this operation
1978  return 1;
1979 }

1990 int4 ActionSetCasts::castInput(PcodeOp *op,int4 slot,Funcdata &data,CastStrategy *castStrategy)
1991 
1992 {
1993  Datatype *ct;
1994  Varnode *vn;
1995  PcodeOp *newop;
1996 
1997  ct = op->getOpcode()->getInputCast(op,slot,castStrategy); // Input type expected by this operation
1998  if (ct == (Datatype *)0) {
1999  if (op->markExplicitUnsigned(slot)) // Decide if this input should be explicitly printed as unsigned constant
2000  return 1;
2001  return 0;
2002  }
2003 
2004  vn = op->getIn(slot);
2005  // Check to make sure we don't have a double cast
2006  if (vn->isWritten() && (vn->getDef()->code() == CPUI_CAST)) {
2007  if (vn->isImplied() && (vn->loneDescend() == op)) {
2008  vn->updateType(ct,false,false);
2009  if (vn->getType()==ct)
2010  return 1;
2011  }
2012  }
2013  else if (vn->isConstant()) {
2014  vn->updateType(ct,false,false);
2015  if (vn->getType() == ct)
2016  return 1;
2017  }
2018  newop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
2019  vn = data.newUniqueOut(op->getIn(slot)->getSize(),newop);
2020  vn->updateType(ct,false,false);
2021  vn->setImplied();
2022 #ifdef CPUI_STATISTICS
2023  data.getArch()->stats->countCast();
2024 #endif
2025  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_CAST);
2026  data.opSetInput(newop,op->getIn(slot),0);
2027  data.opSetInput(op,vn,slot);
2028  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op); // Cast comes AFTER operation
2029  return 1;
2030 }

2032 int4 ActionSetCasts::apply(Funcdata &data)
2033 
2034 {
2035  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
2036  PcodeOp *op;
2037 
2038  data.startCastPhase();
2039  CastStrategy *castStrategy = data.getArch()->print->getCastStrategy();
2040  // We follow data flow, doing basic blocks in dominance order
2041  // Doing operations in basic block order
2042  const BlockGraph &basicblocks( data.getBasicBlocks() );
2043  for(int4 j=0;j<basicblocks.getSize();++j) {
2044  BlockBasic *bb = (BlockBasic *)basicblocks.getBlock(j);
2045  for(iter=bb->beginOp();iter!=bb->endOp();++iter) {
2046  op = *iter;
2047  if (op->notPrinted()) continue;
2048  if (op->code() == CPUI_CAST) continue;
2049  for(int4 i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) // Do input casts first, as output may depend on input
2050  count += castInput(op,i,data,castStrategy);
2051  if (op->code() == CPUI_LOAD) {
2052  TypePointer *ptrtype = (TypePointer *)op->getIn(1)->getHigh()->getType();
2053  int4 valsize = op->getOut()->getSize();
2054  if ((ptrtype->getMetatype()!=TYPE_PTR)||
2055  (ptrtype->getPtrTo()->getSize() != valsize))
2056  data.warning("Load size is inaccurate",op->getAddr());
2057  }
2058  else if (op->code() == CPUI_STORE) {
2059  TypePointer *ptrtype = (TypePointer *)op->getIn(1)->getHigh()->getType();
2060  int4 valsize = op->getIn(2)->getSize();
2061  if ((ptrtype->getMetatype()!=TYPE_PTR)||
2062  (ptrtype->getPtrTo()->getSize() != valsize))
2063  data.warning("Store size is inaccurate",op->getAddr());
2064  }
2065  Varnode *vn = op->getOut();
2066  if (vn == (Varnode *)0) continue;
2067  count += castOutput(op,data,castStrategy);
2068  }
2069  }
2070  return 0; // Indicate full completion

2288 int4 ActionMarkExplicit::baseExplicit(Varnode *vn,int4 maxref)
2289 
2290 {
2291  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
2292 
2293  PcodeOp *def = vn->getDef();
2294  if (def == (PcodeOp *)0) return -1;
2295  if (def->isMarker()) return -1;
2296  if (def->isCall()) {
2297  if ((def->code() == CPUI_NEW)&&(def->numInput() == 1))
2298  return -2; // Explicit, but may need special printing
2299  return -1;
2300  }
2301  HighVariable *high = vn->getHigh();
2302  if ((high!=(HighVariable *)0)&&(high->numInstances()>1)) return -1; // Must not be merged at all
2303  if (vn->isAddrTied()) { // We need to see addrtied as explicit because pointers may reference it
2304  if (def->code() == CPUI_SUBPIECE) {
2305  Varnode *vin = def->getIn(0);
2306  if (vin->isAddrTied()) {
2307  if (vn->overlap(*vin) == def->getIn(1)->getOffset())
2308  return -1; // Should be explicit, will be a copymarker and not printed
2309  }
2310  }
2311  // (Part of) an addrtied location into itself is hopefully implicit
2312  bool shouldbeimplicit = true;
2313  for(iter=vn->beginDescend();iter!=vn->endDescend();++iter) {
2314  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
2315  if ((op->code()!=CPUI_INT_ZEXT)&&(op->code()!=CPUI_PIECE)) {
2316  shouldbeimplicit = false;
2317  break;
2318  }
2319  Varnode *vnout = op->getOut();
2320  if ((!vnout->isAddrTied())||(0!=vnout->contains(*vn))) {
2321  shouldbeimplicit = false;
2322  break;
2323  }
2324  }
2325  if (!shouldbeimplicit) return -1;
2326  }
2327  else if (vn->isMapped()) {
2328  // If NOT addrtied but is still mapped, there must be either a first use (register) mapping
2329  // or a dynamic mapping causing the bit to be set. In either case, it should probably be explicit
2330  return -1;
2331  }
2332  if (vn->hasNoDescend()) return -1; // Must have at least one descendant
2333 
2334  if (def->code() == CPUI_PTRSUB) { // A dereference
2335  Varnode *basevn = def->getIn(0);
2336  if (basevn->isSpacebase()) { // of a spacebase
2337  if (basevn->isConstant() || basevn->isInput())
2338  maxref = 1000000; // Should always be implicit, so remove limit on max references
2339  }
2340  }
2341  int4 desccount = 0;
2342  for(iter=vn->beginDescend();iter!=vn->endDescend();++iter) {
2343  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
2344  if (op->isMarker()) return -1;
2345  desccount += 1;
2346  if (desccount > maxref) return -1; // Must not exceed max descendants
2347  }
2348 
2349  return desccount;
2350 }

2514  if (desccount < 0) {
2515  vn->setExplicit();
2516  count += 1;
2517  if (desccount < -1)
2518  checkNewToConstructor(data,vn);
2519  }
2520  else if (desccount > 1) { // Keep track of possible implieds with more than one descendant
2521  vn->setMark();
2522  multlist.push_back(vn);
2523  }
2524  }
2525 
2526  count += multipleInteraction(multlist);
2527  int4 maxdup = data.getArch()->max_term_duplication;
2528  for(int4 i=0;i<multlist.size();++i) {
2529  Varnode *vn = multlist[i];
2530  if (vn->isMark()) // Mark may have been cleared by multipleInteraction
2531  processMultiplier(vn,maxdup);
2532  }
2533  for(int4 i=0;i<multlist.size();++i)
2534  multlist[i]->clearMark();
2535  return 0;

2567 bool ActionMarkImplied::isPossibleAlias(Varnode *vn1,Varnode *vn2,int4 depth)
2568 
2569 {
2570  if (vn1 == vn2) return true; // Definite alias
2571  if ((!vn1->isWritten())||(!vn2->isWritten())) {
2572  if (vn1->isConstant() && vn2->isConstant())
2573  return (vn1->getOffset()==vn2->getOffset()); // FIXME: these could be NEAR each other and still have an alias
2574  return isPossibleAliasStep(vn1,vn2);
2575  }
2576 
2577  if (!isPossibleAliasStep(vn1,vn2))
2578  return false;
2579  Varnode *cvn1,*cvn2;
2580  PcodeOp *op1 = vn1->getDef();
2581  PcodeOp *op2 = vn2->getDef();
2582  OpCode opc1 = op1->code();
2583  OpCode opc2 = op2->code();
2584  int4 mult1 = 1;
2585  int4 mult2 = 1;
2586  if (opc1 == CPUI_PTRSUB)
2587  opc1 = CPUI_INT_ADD;
2588  else if (opc1 == CPUI_PTRADD) {
2589  opc1 = CPUI_INT_ADD;
2590  mult1 = (int4) op1->getIn(2)->getOffset();
2591  }
2592  if (opc2 == CPUI_PTRSUB)
2593  opc2 = CPUI_INT_ADD;
2594  else if (opc2 == CPUI_PTRADD) {
2595  opc2 = CPUI_INT_ADD;
2596  mult2 = (int4) op2->getIn(2)->getOffset();
2597  }
2598  if (opc1 != opc2) return true;
2599  if (depth == 0) return true; // Couldn't find absolute difference
2600  depth -= 1;
2601  switch(opc1) {
2602  case CPUI_COPY:
2603  case CPUI_INT_ZEXT:
2604  case CPUI_INT_SEXT:
2605  case CPUI_INT_2COMP:
2606  case CPUI_INT_NEGATE:
2607  return isPossibleAlias(op1->getIn(0),op2->getIn(0),depth);
2608  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
2609  cvn1 = op1->getIn(1);
2610  cvn2 = op2->getIn(1);
2611  if (cvn1->isConstant() && cvn2->isConstant()) {
2612  uintb val1 = mult1 * cvn1->getOffset();
2613  uintb val2 = mult2 * cvn2->getOffset();
2614  if (val1 == val2)
2615  return isPossibleAlias(op1->getIn(0),op2->getIn(0),depth);
2616  return !functionalEquality(op1->getIn(0),op2->getIn(0));
2617  }
2618  if (mult1 != mult2) return true;
2619  if (functionalEquality(op1->getIn(0),op2->getIn(0)))
2620  return isPossibleAlias(op1->getIn(1),op2->getIn(1),depth);
2621  if (functionalEquality(op1->getIn(1),op2->getIn(1)))
2622  return isPossibleAlias(op1->getIn(0),op2->getIn(0),depth);
2623  if (functionalEquality(op1->getIn(0),op2->getIn(1)))
2624  return isPossibleAlias(op1->getIn(1),op2->getIn(0),depth);
2625  if (functionalEquality(op1->getIn(1),op2->getIn(0)))
2626  return isPossibleAlias(op1->getIn(0),op2->getIn(1),depth);
2627  break;
2628  default:
2629  break;
2630  }
2631  return true;
2632 }

2640 bool ActionMarkImplied::checkImpliedCover(Funcdata &data,Varnode *vn)
2641 
2642 {
2643  PcodeOp *op,*storeop,*callop;
2644  Varnode *defvn;
2645  int4 i;
2646 
2647  op = vn->getDef();
2648  if (op->code() == CPUI_LOAD) { // Check for loads crossing stores
2649  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator oiter,iterend;
2650  iterend = data.endOp(CPUI_STORE);
2651  for(oiter=data.beginOp(CPUI_STORE);oiter!=iterend;++oiter) {
2652  storeop = *oiter;
2653  if (storeop->isDead()) continue;
2654  if (vn->getCover()->contain(storeop,2)) {
2655  // The LOAD crosses a STORE. We are cavalier
2656  // and let it through unless we can verify
2657  // that the pointers are actually the same
2658  if (storeop->getIn(0)->getOffset() == op->getIn(0)->getOffset()) {

2660  if (isPossibleAlias(storeop->getIn(1),op->getIn(1),2)) return false;
2661  }
2662  }
2663  }
2664  }
2665  if (op->isCall() || (op->code() == CPUI_LOAD)) { // loads crossing calls
2666  for(i=0;i<data.numCalls();++i) {
2667  callop = data.getCallSpecs(i)->getOp();
2668  if (vn->getCover()->contain(callop,2)) return false;
2669  }
2670  }
2671  for(i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) {
2672  defvn = op->getIn(i);
2673  if (defvn->isConstant()) continue;
2674  if (data.getMerge().inflateTest(defvn,vn->getHigh())) // Test for intersection
2675  return false;
2676  }
2677  return true;

2680 int4 ActionMarkImplied::apply(Funcdata &data)
2681 
2682 {
2683  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator viter;
2684  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator oiter;
2685  Varnode *vn,*vncur,*defvn,*outvn;
2686  PcodeOp *op;
2687  vector<DescTreeElement> varstack; // Depth first varnode traversal stack
2688 
2689  for(viter=data.beginLoc();viter!=data.endLoc();++viter) {
2690  vn = *viter;
2691  if (vn->isFree()) continue;
2692  if (vn->isExplicit()) continue;
2693  if (vn->isImplied()) continue;

2697  if (varstack.back().desciter == vncur->endDescend()) {

2699  count += 1; // Will be marked either explicit or implied

2702  else {

2711  data.getMerge().inflate(defvn,vncur->getHigh());

2714  varstack.pop_back();
2715  }
2716  else {
2717  outvn = (*varstack.back().desciter++)->getOut();

2719  if ((!outvn->isExplicit())&&(!outvn->isImplied()))
2720  varstack.push_back(outvn);
2721  }
2722  }
2723  } while(!varstack.empty());
2724  }

2849 void ActionDeadCode::propagateConsumed(vector<Varnode *> &worklist)
2850 
2851 {
2852  Varnode *vn = worklist.back();
2853  worklist.pop_back();
2854  uintb outc = vn->getConsume();
2855  vn->clearConsumeList();
2856 
2857  PcodeOp *op = vn->getDef(); // Assume vn is written
2858 
2859  int4 sz;
2860  uintb a,b;
2861 
2862  switch(op->code()) {
2863  case CPUI_INT_MULT:
2864  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
2865  case CPUI_INT_SUB:
2866  a = outc | (outc>>1); // Make sure all 1 bits below
2867  a = a | (a>>2); // highest 1 bit are set
2868  a = a | (a>>4);
2869  a = a | (a>>8);
2870  a = a | (a>>16);
2871  a = a | (a>>32);
2872  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2873  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2874  break;
2875  case CPUI_SUBPIECE:
2876  sz = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
2877  if (sz >= sizeof(uintb)) // If we are truncating beyond the precision of the consume field
2878  a = 0; // this tells us nothing about consuming bits within the field
2879  else
2880  a = outc << (sz*8);
2881  if ((a==0)&&(outc!=0)&&(op->getIn(0)->getSize() > sizeof(uintb))) {
2882  // If the consumed mask is zero because
2883  // it isn't big enough to cover the whole varnode and
2884  // there are still upper bits that are consumed
2885  a = ~((uintb)0);
2886  a = a ^ (a >> 1); // Set the highest bit possible in the mask to indicate some consumption
2887  }
2888  b = (outc == 0) ? 0 : ~((uintb)0);
2889  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2890  pushConsumed(b,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2891  break;
2892  case CPUI_PIECE:
2893  sz = op->getIn(1)->getSize();
2894  if (vn->getSize() > sizeof(uintb)) { // If the concatenation goes beyond the consume precision
2895  if (sz >= sizeof(uintb)) {
2896  a = ~((uintb)0); // Assume the bits not in the consume field are consumed
2897  b = outc;
2898  }
2899  else {
2900  a = (outc >> (sz*8)) ^ ( (~((uintb)0)) << 8*(sizeof(uintb)-sz));
2901  b = outc ^ (a << (sz*8));
2902  }
2903  }
2904  else {
2905  a = outc >> (sz*8);
2906  b = outc ^ (a << (sz*8));
2907  }
2908  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2909  pushConsumed(b,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2910  break;
2911  case CPUI_INDIRECT:
2912  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2913  if (op->getIn(1)->getSpace()->getType()==IPTR_IOP) {
2914  PcodeOp *indop = PcodeOp::getOpFromConst(op->getIn(1)->getAddr());
2915  if (!indop->isDead()) {
2916  if (indop->code() == CPUI_COPY) {
2917  if (indop->getOut()->characterizeOverlap(*op->getOut())>0) {
2918  pushConsumed(~((uintb)0),indop->getOut(),worklist); // Mark the copy as consumed
2919  indop->setIndirectSource();
2920  }
2921  // If we reach here, there isn't a true block of INDIRECT (RuleIndirectCollapse will convert it to COPY)
2922  }
2923  else
2924  indop->setIndirectSource();
2925  }
2926  }
2927  break;
2928  case CPUI_COPY:
2929  case CPUI_INT_NEGATE:
2930  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2931  break;
2932  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
2933  case CPUI_INT_OR:
2934  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2935  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2936  break;
2937  case CPUI_INT_AND:
2938  if (op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) {
2939  uintb val = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
2940  pushConsumed(outc&val,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2941  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2942  }
2943  else {
2944  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2945  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2946  }
2947  break;
2948  case CPUI_MULTIEQUAL:
2949  for(int4 i=0;i<op->numInput();++i)
2950  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(i),worklist);
2951  break;
2952  case CPUI_INT_ZEXT:
2953  pushConsumed(outc,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2954  break;
2955  case CPUI_INT_SEXT:
2956  b = calc_mask(op->getIn(0)->getSize());
2957  a = outc & b;
2958  if (outc > b)
2959  a |= (b ^ (b>>1)); // Make sure signbit is marked used
2960  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2961  break;
2962  case CPUI_INT_LEFT:
2963  if (op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) {
2964  sz = vn->getSize();
2965  int4 sa = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
2966  if (sz > sizeof(uintb)) { // If there exists bits beyond the precision of the consume field
2967  if (sa >= 8*sizeof(uintb))
2968  a = ~((uintb)0); // Make sure we assume one bits where we shift in unrepresented bits
2969  else
2970  a = (outc >> sa) ^ ( (~((uintb)0)) << (8*sizeof(uintb)-sa));
2971  sz = 8*sz -sa;
2972  if (sz < 8*sizeof(uintb)) {
2973  uintb mask = ~((uintb)0);
2974  mask <<= sz;
2975  a = a & ~mask; // Make sure high bits that are left shifted out are not marked consumed
2976  }
2977  }
2978  else
2979  a = outc >> sa; // Most cases just do this
2980  b = (outc == 0) ? 0 : ~((uintb)0);
2981  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2982  pushConsumed(b,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2983  }
2984  else {
2985  a = (outc==0) ? 0 : ~((uintb)0);
2986  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2987  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(1),worklist);
2988  }
2989  break;
2990  case CPUI_INT_RIGHT:
2991  if (op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) {
2992  int4 sa = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
2993  if (sa >= 8*sizeof(uintb)) // If the shift is beyond the precision of the consume field
2994  a = 0; // We know nothing about the low order consumption of the input bits
2995  else
2996  a = outc << sa; // Most cases just do this
2997  b = (outc == 0) ? 0 : ~((uintb)0);
2998  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
2999  pushConsumed(b,op->getIn(1),worklist);
3000  }
3001  else {
3002  a = (outc==0) ? 0 : ~((uintb)0);
3003  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
3004  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(1),worklist);
3005  }
3006  break;
3007  case CPUI_INT_LESS:
3008  case CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL:
3009  case CPUI_INT_EQUAL:
3010  case CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL:
3011  if (outc==0)
3012  a = 0;
3013  else // Anywhere we know is zero, is not getting "consumed"
3014  a = op->getIn(0)->getNZMask() | op->getIn(1)->getNZMask();
3015  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(0),worklist);
3016  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(1),worklist);
3017  break;
3018  default:
3019  a = (outc==0) ? 0 : ~((uintb)0); // all or nothing
3020  for(int4 i=0;i<op->numInput();++i)
3021  pushConsumed(a,op->getIn(i),worklist);
3022  break;
3023  }
3024 
3025 }

3059 int4 ActionDeadCode::apply(Funcdata &data)
3060 
3061 {
3062  int4 i;
3063  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
3064  PcodeOp *op;
3065  Varnode *vn;
3066  vector<Varnode *> worklist;
3067  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator viter,endviter;
3068  const AddrSpaceManager *manage = data.getArch();
3069  AddrSpace *spc;
3070 
3071  // Clear consume flags
3072  for(viter=data.beginLoc();viter!=data.endLoc();++viter) {
3073  vn = *viter;
3074  vn->clearConsumeList();
3075  vn->clearConsumeVacuous();
3076  vn->setConsume(0);
3077  if (vn->isAddrForce()&&(!vn->isDirectWrite()))
3078  vn->clearAddrForce();
3079  }
3080 
3081  // Set pre-live registers
3082  for(i=0;i<manage->numSpaces();++i) {
3083  spc = manage->getSpace(i);
3084  if (!spc->doesDeadcode()) continue;
3085  if (data.deadRemovalAllowed(spc)) continue; // Mark consumed if we have NOT heritaged
3086  viter = data.beginLoc(spc);
3087  endviter = data.endLoc(spc);
3088  while(viter != endviter) {
3089  vn = *viter++;
3090  pushConsumed(~((uintb)0),vn,worklist);
3091  }
3092  }
3093 
3094  for(iter=data.beginOpAlive();iter!=data.endOpAlive();++iter) {
3095  op = *iter;
3096

3689  newvn = vn->getDef()->getIn(0);
3690  else {

3692  if ((castop != (PcodeOp *)0)&&(castop->code() == CPUI_CAST))
3693  newvn = castop->getOut();
3694  }
3695  // See if the varnode on the other side is explicit
3696  if ((newvn != (Varnode *)0)&&(newvn->isExplicit()))
3697  vn = newvn; // in which case we use it
3698  }
3699 
3700  int4 offset;
3701  if (!entry.isPiece())
3702  offset = -1;
3703  else
3704  offset = entry.getOffset();
3705  vn->getHigh()->setSymbol(sym,offset);
3706  if (!sym->isTypeLocked()) { // If the dynamic symbol did not lock its type
3707  localmap->retypeSymbol(sym,vn->getType()); // use the type propagated into the varnode
3708  }
3709  else if (sym->getType() != vn->getType()) {
3710  ostringstream s;
3711  s << "Unable to use type for symbol " << sym->getName();
3712  data.warningHeader(s.str());
3713  localmap->retypeSymbol(sym,vn->getType()); // use the type propagated into the varnode
3714  }
3715  // FIXME: Setting the symbol here (for the first time) gives the type no time to propagate properly
3716  // Currently the casts aren't set properly
3717 
3718  count += 1;
3719  }
3720  return 0;
3721 }

3936 bool ActionInferTypes::propagateGoodEdge(PcodeOp *op,int4 inslot,int4 outslot,Varnode *invn)
3937 
3938 {
3939  if (inslot == outslot) return false; // don't backtrack
3940  type_metatype metain = invn->getTempType()->getMetatype();
3941  switch(op->code()) {
3942  case CPUI_NEW:
3943  if ((inslot != 0)||(outslot != -1)) return false;
3944  break;
3945  case CPUI_INDIRECT:
3946  if (op->isIndirectCreation()) return false;
3947  if ((inslot==1)||(outslot==1)) return false;
3948  if ((inslot!=-1)&&(outslot!=-1)) return false; // Must propagate input <-> output
3949  break;
3950  case CPUI_COPY:
3951  if ((inslot!=-1)&&(outslot!=-1)) return false; // Must propagate input <-> output
3952  if (metain == TYPE_BOOL) {
3953  if (inslot != -1) return false;
3954  Varnode *othervn = op->getIn(outslot);
3955  if (!othervn->isConstant()) return false;
3956  uintb val = othervn->getOffset();
3957  if (val > 1)
3958  return false;
3959  }
3960  break;
3961  case CPUI_MULTIEQUAL:
3962  if ((inslot!=-1)&&(outslot!=-1)) return false; // Must propagate input <-> output
3963  break;
3964  case CPUI_INT_LESS:
3965  case CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL:
3966  if ((inslot==-1)||(outslot==-1)) return false; // Must propagate input <-> input
3967  if (metain == TYPE_BOOL) return false;
3968  break;
3969  case CPUI_INT_EQUAL:
3970  case CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL:
3971  if ((inslot==-1)||(outslot==-1)) return false; // Must propagate input <-> input
3972  if (metain == TYPE_BOOL) { // Only propagate bool to 0 or 1 const
3973  Varnode *othervn = op->getIn(outslot);
3974  if (!othervn->isConstant()) return false;
3975  uintb val = othervn->getOffset();
3976  if (val > 1)
3977  return false;
3978  }
3979  break;
3980  case CPUI_LOAD:
3981  case CPUI_STORE:
3982  if ((inslot==0)||(outslot==0)) return false; // Don't propagate along this edge
3983  if (invn->isSpacebase()) return false;
3984  if (metain == TYPE_BOOL) return false;
3985  break;
3986  case CPUI_PTRADD:
3987  if ((inslot==2)||(outslot==2)) return false; // Don't propagate along this edge
3988  case CPUI_PTRSUB:
3989  if ((inslot!=-1)&&(outslot!=-1)) return false; // Must propagate input <-> output
3990  if (metain != TYPE_PTR) return false;
3991  break;
3992  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
3993  if (metain != TYPE_PTR) {
3994  if ((metain == TYPE_INT)||(metain == TYPE_UINT)) {
3995  if ((outslot==1) && (op->getIn(1)->isConstant()))
3996  return true;
3997  }
3998  return false;
3999  }
4000  if ((inslot!=-1)&&(outslot!=-1)) return false; // Must propagate input <-> output
4001  break;
4002  case CPUI_SEGMENTOP:
4003  // Must propagate slot2 <-> output
4004  if ((inslot==0)||(inslot==1)) return false;
4005  if ((outslot==0)||(outslot==1)) return false;
4006  if (invn->isSpacebase()) return false;
4007  if (metain != TYPE_PTR) return false;
4008  break;
4009  case CPUI_INT_AND:
4010  case CPUI_INT_OR:
4011  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
4012  if (!invn->getTempType()->isPowerOfTwo()) return false; // Only propagate flag enums
4013  break;
4014  default:
4015  return false;
4016  }
4017  return true;
4018 }

4032 bool ActionInferTypes::propagateTypeEdge(TypeFactory *typegrp,PcodeOp *op,int4 inslot,int4 outslot)
4033 
4034 {
4035  Varnode *invn,*outvn;
4036  Datatype *newtype;
4037 
4038  outvn = (outslot==-1) ? op->getOut() : op->getIn(outslot);
4039  if (outvn->isAnnotation()) return false;
4040  if (outvn->isTypeLock()) return false; // Can't propagate through typelock
4041  invn = (inslot==-1) ? op->getOut() : op->getIn(inslot);
4042  Datatype *alttype = invn->getTempType();
4043  if (!propagateGoodEdge(op,inslot,outslot,invn))
4044  return false;
4045 
4046  switch(op->code()) {
4047  case CPUI_INDIRECT:
4048  case CPUI_COPY:
4049  case CPUI_MULTIEQUAL:
4050  case CPUI_INT_LESS:
4051  case CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL:
4052  case CPUI_INT_EQUAL:
4053  case CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL:
4054  case CPUI_INT_AND:
4055  case CPUI_INT_OR:
4056  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
4057  if (invn->isSpacebase()) {
4058  AddrSpace *spc = typegrp->getArch()->getDefaultSpace();
4059  newtype = typegrp->getTypePointer(alttype->getSize(),typegrp->getBase(1,TYPE_UNKNOWN),spc->getWordSize());
4060  }
4061  else
4062  newtype = alttype;
4063  break;
4064  case CPUI_NEW:
4065  {
4066  Varnode *invn = op->getIn(0);
4067  if (!invn->isWritten()) return false; // Don't propagate
4068  if (invn->getDef()->code() != CPUI_CPOOLREF) return false;
4069  newtype = alttype; // Propagate cpool result as result of new operator
4070  }
4071  break;
4072  case CPUI_SEGMENTOP:
4073  {
4074  AddrSpace *spc = typegrp->getArch()->getDefaultSpace();
4075  Datatype *btype = ((TypePointer *)alttype)->getPtrTo();
4076  newtype = typegrp->getTypePointer(outvn->getSize(),btype,spc->getWordSize());
4077  }
4078  break;
4079  case CPUI_LOAD:
4080  if (inslot == -1) { // Propagating output to input (value to ptr)
4081  AddrSpace *spc = Address::getSpaceFromConst(op->getIn(0)->getAddr());
4082  newtype = typegrp->getTypePointerNoDepth(outvn->getTempType()->getSize(),alttype,spc->getWordSize());
4083  }
4084  else if (alttype->getMetatype()==TYPE_PTR) {
4085  newtype = ((TypePointer *)alttype)->getPtrTo();
4086  if (newtype->getSize() != outvn->getTempType()->getSize()) // Size must be appropriate
4087  newtype = outvn->getTempType();
4088  }
4089  else
4090  newtype = outvn->getTempType(); // Don't propagate anything
4091  break;
4092  case CPUI_STORE:
4093  if (inslot==2) { // Propagating value to ptr
4094  AddrSpace *spc = Address::getSpaceFromConst(op->getIn(0)->getAddr());
4095  newtype = typegrp->getTypePointerNoDepth(outvn->getTempType()->getSize(),alttype,spc->getWordSize());
4096  }
4097  else if (alttype->getMetatype()==TYPE_PTR) {
4098  newtype = ((TypePointer *)alttype)->getPtrTo();
4099  if (newtype->getSize() != outvn->getTempType()->getSize())
4100  newtype = outvn->getTempType();
4101  }
4102  else
4103  newtype = outvn->getTempType(); // Don't propagate anything
4104  break;
4105  case CPUI_PTRADD:
4106  case CPUI_PTRSUB:
4107  if (inslot == -1) // Propagating output to input
4108  newtype = op->getIn(outslot)->getTempType(); // Don't propagate pointer types this direction
4109  else
4110  newtype = propagateAddIn2Out(typegrp,op,inslot);
4111  break;
4112  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
4113  if (outvn->isConstant() && (alttype->getMetatype() != TYPE_PTR))
4114  newtype = alttype;
4115  else if (inslot == -1) // Propagating output to input
4116  newtype = op->getIn(outslot)->getTempType(); // Don't propagate pointer types this direction
4117  else
4118  newtype = propagateAddIn2Out(typegrp,op,inslot);
4119  break;
4120  default:
4121  return false; // Don't propagate along this edge
4122  }
4123  if (0>newtype->typeOrder(*outvn->getTempType())) {
4124 #ifdef TYPEPROP_DEBUG
4125  propagationDebug(typegrp->getArch(),outvn,newtype,op,inslot,(Varnode *)0);
4126 #endif
4127  outvn->setTempType(newtype);
4128  return !outvn->isMark();
4129  }
4130  return false;
4131 }

4159

4191 void ActionInferTypes::propagateOneType(TypeFactory *typegrp,Varnode *vn)
4192 
4193 {
4194  PropagationState *ptr;
4195  vector<PropagationState> state;
4196 
4197  state.push_back(PropagationState(vn));
4198  vn->setMark();
4199 
4200  while(!state.empty()) {
4201  ptr = &state.back();
4202  if (!ptr->valid()) { // If we are out of edges to traverse
4203  ptr->vn->clearMark();
4204  state.pop_back();
4205  }
4206  else {
4207  if (propagateTypeEdge(typegrp,ptr->op,ptr->inslot,ptr->slot)) {
4208  vn = (ptr->slot==-1) ? ptr->op->getOut() : ptr->op->getIn(ptr->slot);
4209  ptr->step(); // Make sure to step before push_back
4210  state.push_back(PropagationState(vn));
4211  vn->setMark();
4212  }
4213  else
4214  ptr->step();
4215  }
4216  }

4227 void ActionInferTypes::propagateRef(Funcdata &data,Varnode *vn,const Address &addr)
4228 
4229 {
4230  Datatype *ct = vn->getTempType();
4231  if (ct->getMetatype() != TYPE_PTR) return;
4232  ct = ((TypePointer *)ct)->getPtrTo();
4233  if (ct->getMetatype() == TYPE_SPACEBASE) return;
4234  if (ct->getMetatype() == TYPE_UNKNOWN) return; // Don't bother propagating this
4235  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator iter,enditer;
4236  uintb off = addr.getOffset();
4237  TypeFactory *typegrp = data.getArch()->types;
4238  Address endaddr = addr + ct->getSize();
4239  if (endaddr.getOffset() < off) // If the address wrapped
4240  enditer = data.endLoc(addr.getSpace()); // Go to end of space
4241  else
4242  enditer = data.endLoc(endaddr);
4243  iter = data.beginLoc(addr);
4244  uintb lastoff = 0;
4245  int4 lastsize = ct->getSize();
4246  Datatype *lastct = ct;
4247  while(iter != enditer) {
4248  Varnode *curvn = *iter;
4249  ++iter;
4250  if (curvn->isAnnotation()) continue;
4251  if ((!curvn->isWritten())&&curvn->hasNoDescend()) continue;
4252  uintb curoff = curvn->getOffset() - off;
4253  int4 cursize = curvn->getSize();
4254  if (curoff + cursize > ct->getSize()) continue;
4255  if ((cursize!=lastsize)||(curoff!=lastoff)) {
4256  lastoff = curoff;
4257  lastsize = cursize;
4258  Datatype *cur = ct;
4259  do {
4260  lastct = cur;
4261  cur = cur->getSubType(curoff,&curoff);
4262  } while(cur != (Datatype *)0);
4263  }
4264  if (lastct->getSize() != cursize) continue;
4265 
4266  // Try to propagate the reference type into a varnode that is pointed to by that reference
4267  if (0>lastct->typeOrder(*curvn->getTempType())) {
4268 #ifdef TYPEPROP_DEBUG
4269  propagationDebug(data.getArch(),curvn,lastct,(PcodeOp *)0,0,vn);
4270 #endif
4271  curvn->setTempType(lastct);
4272  propagateOneType(typegrp,curvn); // Try to propagate the new type as far as possible
4273  }
4274  }
4275 }

4328 int4 ActionInferTypes::apply(Funcdata &data)
4329 
4330 {
4331  // Make sure spacebase is accurate or bases could get typed and then ptrarithed
4332  if (!data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) return 0;
4333  TypeFactory *typegrp = data.getArch()->types;
4334  Varnode *vn;
4335  VarnodeLocSet::const_iterator iter;
4336 
4337 #ifdef TYPEPROP_DEBUG
4338  ostringstream s;
4339  s << "Type propagation pass - " << dec << localcount;
4340  data.getArch()->printDebug(s.str());
4341 #endif
4342  if (localcount >= 7) { // This constant arrived at empirically
4343  if (localcount == 7) {
4344  data.warningHeader("Type propagation algorithm not settling");
4345  localcount += 1;
4346  }
4347  return 0;
4348  }
4349  buildLocaltypes(data); // Set up initial types (based on local info)
4350  for(iter=data.beginLoc();iter!=data.endLoc();++iter) {
4351  vn = *iter;
4352  if (vn->isAnnotation()) continue;
4353  if ((!vn->isWritten())&&(vn->hasNoDescend())) continue;
4354  propagateOneType(typegrp,vn);
4355  }
4356  AddrSpace *spcid = data.getScopeLocal()->getSpaceId();
4357  Varnode *spcvn = data.findSpacebaseInput(spcid);
4358  if (spcvn != (Varnode *)0)
4359  propagateSpacebaseRef(data,spcvn);
4360  if (writeBack(data)) {
4361  // count += 1; // Do not consider this a data-flow change
4362  localcount += 1;
4363  }
4364  return 0;
4365 }
4366 
4369 void TermOrder::collect(void)
4370 
4371 {
4372  Varnode *curvn;
4373  PcodeOp *curop;
4374  PcodeOp *subop,*multop;
4375 
4376  vector<PcodeOp *> opstack; // Depth first traversal path
4377  vector<PcodeOp *> multstack;
4378 
4379  opstack.push_back(root);
4380  multstack.push_back((PcodeOp *)0);
4381 
4382  while(!opstack.empty()) {
4383  curop = opstack.back();
4384  multop = multstack.back();
4385  opstack.pop_back();
4386  multstack.pop_back();
4387  for(int4 i=0;i<curop->numInput();++i) {
4388  curvn = curop->getIn(i); // curvn is a node of the subtree IF
4389  if (!curvn->isWritten()) { // curvn is not defined by another operation
4390  terms.push_back(PcodeOpEdge(curop,i,multop));
4391  continue;
4392  }
4393  if (curvn->loneDescend() == (PcodeOp *)0) { // curvn has more then one use
4394  terms.push_back(PcodeOpEdge(curop,i,multop));
4395  continue;
4396  }
4397  subop = curvn->getDef();
4398  if (subop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) { // or if curvn is defined with some other type of op
4399  if ((subop->code()==CPUI_INT_MULT)&&(subop->getIn(1)->isConstant())) {
4400  PcodeOp *addop = subop->getIn(0)->getDef();
4401  if ((addop!=(PcodeOp *)0)&&(addop->code()==CPUI_INT_ADD)) {
4402  if (addop->getOut()->loneDescend()!=(PcodeOp *)0) {
4403  opstack.push_back(addop);
4404  multstack.push_back(subop);
4405  continue;
4406  }
4407  }
4408  }
4409  terms.push_back(PcodeOpEdge(curop,i,multop));
4410  continue;
4411  }
4412  opstack.push_back(subop);
4413  multstack.push_back(multop);
4414  }
4415  }
4416 }
4417 
4418 void TermOrder::sortTerms(void)
4419 
4420 {
4421  for(vector<PcodeOpEdge>::iterator iter=terms.begin();iter!=terms.end();++iter)
4422  sorter.push_back( &(*iter) );
4423 
4424  sort(sorter.begin(),sorter.end(),additiveCompare);
4425 }
